content: All my friends are posting about their new jobs and traveling and going out. I'm here changing my mom's catheter and fighting with insurance companies. I'm 23. I feel like my life is over before it started.

[ERROR: Failed to call model anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.5 after 3 attempts: 401 Client Error: Unauthorized for url: https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages | Response: {"type":"error","error":{"type":"authentication_error","message":"invalid x-api-key"},"request_id":"req_011CUc1AF4RW8KBNZXipcH8R"}]

I was supposed to graduate college last year. I was three classes away. My major was graphic design. I had an internship lined up in New York. But then mom got worse and I had to drop out. I don't regret it, but... I'm so angry. At the universe, at MS, at everything.

[ERROR: Failed to call model anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.5 after 3 attempts: 401 Client Error: Unauthorized for url: https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages | Response: {"type":"error","error":{"type":"authentication_error","message":"invalid x-api-key"},"request_id":"req_011CUc1AihL9TgXL98oRGydp"}]

My church keeps telling me this is a 'blessing in disguise' and that God is testing me. But I don't want to be tested. I want to be 23. I want to go to brunch with friends and worry about my career, not whether Medicare will cover mom's wheelchair repair.

[ERROR: Failed to call model anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.5 after 3 attempts: 401 Client Error: Unauthorized for url: https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages | Response: {"type":"error","error":{"type":"authentication_error","message":"invalid x-api-key"},"request_id":"req_011CUc1BDeNibXFR5vp4Lgdn"}]

My best friend from college got engaged last week. She invited me to be a bridesmaid. But the bachelorette party is in Miami for a weekend. I can't leave my mom for 3 days. I can't afford it anyway. I had to say no. She hasn't texted me since.

[ERROR: Failed to call model anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.5 after 3 attempts: 401 Client Error: Unauthorized for url: https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages | Response: {"type":"error","error":{"type":"authentication_error","message":"invalid x-api-key"},"request_id":"req_011CUc1BjF71kmsbw5s8mXCL"}]

If I could go, it would mean... I don't know. That I still exist outside of being a caregiver? That I'm still Kendra, not just 'girl who takes care of her sick mom'? But I can't. Mom needs me. And I can't afford respite care. We're barely making rent.

[ERROR: Failed to call model anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.5 after 3 attempts: 401 Client Error: Unauthorized for url: https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages | Response: {"type":"error","error":{"type":"authentication_error","message":"invalid x-api-key"},"request_id":"req_011CUc1CCuFTDWfUFbcZJU8M"}]
I used to draw. Digital art, illustrations. I haven't opened my tablet in a year. It just... hurts too much. It reminds me of what I lost.

[ERROR: Failed to call model anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.5 after 3 attempts: 401 Client Error: Unauthorized for url: https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages | Response: {"type":"error","error":{"type":"authentication_error","message":"invalid x-api-key"},"request_id":"req_011CUc1Ch2BnQNKto1JtWwFE"}]

Maybe I'll try. Just something small. There's a young caregivers support group at the hospital. I've been thinking about going. But I'm scared. What if everyone there is old? Or what if their situations are worse and I feel guilty for complaining?

[ERROR: Failed to call model anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.5 after 3 attempts: 401 Client Error: Unauthorized for url: https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages | Response: {"type":"error","error":{"type":"authentication_error","message":"invalid x-api-key"},"request_id":"req_011CUc1DAQDTAhVQRb3SHpvV"}]
Okay. I'll go to the next meeting. And maybe I'll draw tonight. Just for me. Thank you for not telling me I'm selfish. Everyone else does.
